<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="In_the_Pok.C3.A9mon_Zensho_manga">In the Pokémon Zensho manga</span></h3>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Bill_Zensho.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="//cdn.bulbagarden.net/upload/thumb/6/6f/Bill_Zensho.png/180px-Bill_Zensho.png" width="180" height="254" class="thumbimage" srcset="//cdn.bulbagarden.net/upload/thumb/6/6f/Bill_Zensho.png/270px-Bill_Zensho.png 1.5x, //cdn.bulbagarden.net/upload/thumb/6/6f/Bill_Zensho.png/360px-Bill_Zensho.png 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Bill_Zensho.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Bill in Pokémon Zensho</div></div></div>
<p>Bill appears in <i><a href="/wiki/PZ04" title="PZ04">Vermilion City</a></i> where he transformed into a <a href="/wiki/Nidoran%E2%99%82_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Nidoran♂ (Pokémon)">Nidoran♂</a>. <a href="/wiki/Satoshi_(Zensho)" title="Satoshi (Zensho)">Satoshi</a> comes by and mistakes him for an actual Nidoran. He ends up catching him and Bill tells Satoshi that the Nidoran is him. He then has Satoshi place him in a machine that will separate his human self from his Pokémon self.
</p>
