<tr style="background:#FFF">
<td>Chinese (<span class="explain" title="Taiwan and mainland China">Mandarin</span>)
</td>
<td>曾根崎正輝 / 曾根崎正辉<br /><i>Cénggēnqí Zhènghuī</i>
</td>
<td>From the Japanese 曾根崎 <i>Sonezaki</i> and 正輝 <i>Masaki</i>. 輝 (radiance) is also a possible reference to his lighthouse on the cape.
</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#FFF">
<td>Thai
</td>
<td>มาซากิ <i>Masaki</i>
</td>
<td>Transliteration of his Japanese name.
</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#FFF">
<td>Vietnamese
</td>
<td>Sonezaki Masaki
</td>
<td>Transliteration of his Japanese name.
</td></tr></table>
